<item>
            <title>[OAK-2099] AIOOBE in Segment#toString</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2099</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Segment#toString&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t account for correcting the offset of a record in a segment in the case where the total segment size is less than the maximal segment size. This usually leads to an AIOOBE at the point where the root refs / blob refs are listed. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
